      "content": "It is understandable to be concerned about your incision site, but redness and mild warmth can sometimes be part of the healing process. However, yellow discharge accompanying these symptoms warrants caution, as it could indicate signs of infection. Please contact your doctor or a healthcare provider in Sydney to have the cyst site properly assessed to ensure it heals without complication. Avoid putting creams or compresses on it until you get professional advice.",
      "source": "target",
